page.description: An important part of writing any program is handling potential errors properly. You should do the same when writing an Xbasic script, making sure it can recover from some common run-time errors (e.g., when a file is not found, the disk is full, or the table is opened exclusively by another session or user).

section.description: To react appropriately to specific run-time errors, you can use the ERROR_CODE_GET() and ERROR_TEXT_GET() functions to obtain the error code and error message returned by the most recent run-time error. Use these functions in an error handling routine (established by an ON ERROR GOTO statement) to compare the error code against one or more of the possible error codes that might occur.
section.note: User-defined error messages should have a number in the range 20000 to 24999.

section.title: How to Structure an Error Handler
section.description: For example, the general format of your error handler might be as follows:
section.example: error_handler: err = error_code_get() select case err = 800 resume next case err = 801 resume next ... case else msg = error_text_get(err) ui_msg_box("Error", msg, UI_ATTENTION_SYMBOL) end end select end

description.p: Each CASE of the SELECT statement is for a different error. If an error occurs for which you have not included a CASE, a default message box will display the error message and then end the script.

item.description: Reserved for User-defined error codes.

description.p: The Session_Folder property is no longer supported. Use Session.SaveDataAsFile() to safely store file-based data in the Session instead of attempting to write directly to disk. See *[link:https://documentation.alphasoftware.com/documentation/index?search=storing%20files%20in%20sessions@https://documentation.alphasoftware.com/documentation/index?search=storing%20files%20in%20sessions]* for additional information.

The Session_Url property is no longer supported. Use Session.FormatFileDataURL() to link to any resources that have been stored in the Session. See *[link:https://documentation.alphasoftware.com/documentation/index?search=storing%20files%20in%20sessions@https://documentation.alphasoftware.com/documentation/index?search=storing%20files%20in%20sessions]* for additional information.

Response.Add_Cookie() is no longer supported. Use Response.Cookies.Add() instead. See *[link:https://documentation.alphasoftware.com/documentation/index?search=server%20replacing%20responseaddcookie%20function@https://documentation.alphasoftware.com/documentation/index?search=server%20replacing%20responseaddcookie%20function]* for more information.

Response.Add_Header() is no longer supported. Use Response.Headers.Add() instead. See *[link:https://documentation.alphasoftware.com/documentation/index?search=replacing%20response.add_header%20function@https://documentation.alphasoftware.com/documentation/index?search=replacing%20response.add_header%20function]* for more information.
Response.Message_Body is a read-only property. Use Response.Write() to add data to the outgoing Response.

a5w_load_aex() is no longer supported. See *[link:https://documentation.alphasoftware.com/documentation/index?search=server%20xb%20change%20in%20way%20aex%20files%20are%20used%20in%20a%20web%20application@https://documentation.alphasoftware.com/documentation/index?search=server%20xb%20change%20in%20way%20aex%20files%20are%20used%20in%20a%20web%20application]* for more information.

a5w_unload_aex() is no longer supported. See *[link:https://documentation.alphasoftware.com/documentation/index?search=server%20xb%20change%20in%20way%20aex%20files%20are%20used%20in%20a%20web%20application@https://documentation.alphasoftware.com/documentation/index?search=server%20xb%20change%20in%20way%20aex%20files%20are%20used%20in%20a%20web%20application]* for more information.
Application.Path() is no longer supported. Use Request.ApplicationRoot as a replacement.

Server.ClearA5ICache() is no longer supported. The A5I cache now automatically monitors the filesystem and does not need to be manually cleared. Use Server.ClearAEXCache() to clear the AEX cache if desired.
Server.ClearGzipCache() is no longer supported. The Gzip cache now automatically monitors the filesystem and does not need to be manually cleared.
Request.Script_Name is no longer supported. Use Request.ScriptName instead.
